HEADWORD: Navew
<hw>Na"vew</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>navel</ets>,
<ets>naveau</ets>, a dim. fr. L. <ets>napus</ets> navew. Cf.
<er>Napiform</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A kind of small turnip,
a variety of <spn>Brassica campestris</spn>. See
<er>Brassica</er>.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>naphew</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

